{
  "stem": "10588.7",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I want to share a poem, which is called 'A Nazi Murderer in Snow White Gloves.' And it was written April 29th, 1982.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The poem was motivated because I remembered a phrase that my family was using.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Yiddish, they used to say-- and I'll explain it in English.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The [YIDDISH], when somebody pretended to be something that he wasn't, and he was cruel or he was, you know, destructive, but pretended to be a gentleman.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my-- my father and mother used to use this expression, [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it so happened that when I arrived to Auschwitz, Mengele was wearing white gloves.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when I was looking at the Nazis in contrast, how they looked nice and clean and-- and well-fed, and we were starved and looked filthy and horrible-- so in a way, it-- it made it for them easier to do to them what they did, because they didn't see us.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They tried to view us as subhuman, as vermin.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So vermin, you're a bug.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If you don't identify with, it's easier to kill, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this is the poem which I wrote.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it's called 'A Nazi Murderer in Snow White Gloves.' 'Snow white gloves are shrouding his blood-stained hands, and his soul is as black as the night of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember him well, standing at the gate of the killing center of Auschwitz in his spotless SS uniform and a swastika on his armband.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He looked so calm, collected, and so convincingly deceptive, intoxicated by the myth of his racial purity and innate superiority.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He willfully carries out Hitler's evil will, instead of God's divine will.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
